Josh, shouldn't you keep the one she gave you and sell or trade the other one?  It's so cool that she got you baseball cards I think it will be a senitmental gift down the road.  Plus, what if she asks to see your set and you have a different Tannehill than the one she gave you?

Huge +1 on this. I would keep this one and sell my other or just keep both - an angry/hurt girlfriend is not worth selling this card at a $12 loss!

It's so cool that she got you baseball cards I think it will be a senitmental gift down the road.  Plus, what if she asks to see your set and you have a different Tannehill than the one she gave you?[/QUOTE]
I concur.  Keep the gift, unload the other.  Sentimental value is more important, and any woman that gives a card as a gift cares and is a keeper.
LOL but a PSA 2.5 is better than a PSA 2.O MK.

Not the right way to think about it man.  Just keep both if you're attached to the first one.  I bet 99% of us on here have never been given a baseball card as a gift from our significant others.  That's pretty special.  Also, happy wife; happy life :)
Lol I now feel like a bad person.
Ah, man.  I was about to offer you $2000 for the other one;).  Good choice keeping it.
